Today was the day of my summer training program in Novam Controls.
The session began with an introduction to computer networks and how important they are, for communication.
A computer network is a group of devices connected together.
They talk to each other to share data and things like files and internet.
The trainer explained that there are kinds of networks.
These include LAN or Local Area Network, MAN or Metropolitan Area Network, WAN or Wide Area Network and PAN or Personal Area Network.
We learned about their features, benefits and real-life uses.
I also learned about the parts of a network.
These include routers, switches and hubs.
There are also access points and network interface cards.
We talked about how data's sent in packets.
Devices use IP addresses to talk to each other.
By the end of the session I understood the basics of networking.
Computer networking is the foundation of cybersecurity.
It helps keep data safe.
The session was very informative.
It gave me an idea of how networking works.
